        "event": "High Wind Warning",
        "headline": "High Wind Warning issued April 26 at 1:56AM AKDT until April 26 at 4:00PM AKDT by NWS Anchorage AK",
        "description": "* WHAT...Southwest winds 45 to 60 mph, with gusts up to 80 mph\nexpected.\n\n* WHERE...Atka and Adak.\n\n* WHEN...Until 4 PM AKDT this afternoon.\n\n* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, and\ncause power outages. Travel will be difficult.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Westerly winds will gust up to 70-80 mph later\nthis morning, then slowly decrease through the afternoon and\nevening.",
        "severity": "Severe",
        "certainty": "Likely",
        "urgency": "Expected",
        "sender": "NWS Anchorage AK",
        "effective": "2026-04-26T01:56:00-08:00",
        "expires": "2026-04-26T16:00:00-08:00",
        "areas": "Atka and Adak",
        "category": "Met",
        "response": "Prepare",
        "instruction": "People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around\nor damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of power outages.",
        "lat": null,
        "lng": null
      },
      {
